{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTHEEs3yDgTUbJsfMvoMta","type":"tool_result","content":"   505→```\n   506→\n   507→A typical `finalize` script checks `$CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and acts accordingly —\n   508→closing the ticket on success, or posting a failure comment for investigation.\n   509→Wiring both results to `done` (not `abort`) ensures the finalize workflow itself\n   510→completes rather than aborting. Note that the overall task status reflects the\n   511→worst outcome of the main and finalize phases — if finalize fails, the task is\n   512→marked as failed even when main succeeded.\n   513→\n   514→**If omitted:** The daemon skips the finalize phase entirely. This is fine if you\n   515→don't need automated cleanup.\n   516→\n   517→### `release-task` — Releasing Stale Claims\n   518→\n   519→The `release-task` workflow handles releasing tasks that are stuck in `in_progress`\n   520→status without an active worker. This happens when a run fails, the daemon restarts,\n   521→or a container is lost. The web dashboard detects these stale tasks and shows a\n   522→**Release** button next to them."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7063410-9e81-4bdd-a303-eb35e073d3d0","uuid":"3ba017ad-df06-4f0b-be0a-0d79e1b8c859","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"```\n\nA typical `finalize` script checks `$CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and acts accordingly —\nclosing the ticket on success, or posting a failure comment for investigation.\nWiring both results to `done` (not `abort`) ensures the finalize workflow itself\ncompletes rather than aborting. Note that the overall task status reflects the\nworst outcome of the main and finalize phases — if finalize fails, the task is\nmarked as failed even when main succeeded.\n\n**If omitted:** The daemon skips the finalize phase entirely. This is fine if you\ndon't need automated cleanup.\n\n### `release-task` — Releasing Stale Claims\n\nThe `release-task` workflow handles releasing tasks that are stuck in `in_progress`\nstatus without an active worker. This happens when a run fails, the daemon restarts,\nor a container is lost. The web dashboard detects these stale tasks and shows a\n**Release** button next to them.","numLines":18,"startLine":505,"totalLines":922}}}
