{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AofUuDRp8n8rw3NCP5PLZz","type":"tool_result","content":"   245→workflow \"finalize\" {\n   246→  step push-for-review {\n   247→    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   248→    results = [success, fail]\n   249→  }\n   250→\n   251→  push-for-review:success -> done\n   252→  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   253→}\n   254→```\n   255→\n   256→The daemon runs `list-tasks` to discover work (output is JSONL), picks an open task,\n   257→runs `main` with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` set, then runs `finalize` regardless of outcome.\n   258→The `list-tasks` script writes one JSON object per line to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`.\n   259→The `main` workflow receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket.\n   260→The `finalize` workflow decides what to do based on the outcome (available via\n   261→`CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars).\n   262→\n   263→## Execution Model\n   264→\n   265→**Container workflows** are parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside a Docker\n   266→container. The agent walks the graph: execute current step, read its result, follow the\n   267→wiring to the next step. This continues until a terminal (`done` or `abort`) is reached.\n   268→All steps run inside the same container. File state accumulates naturally across steps.\n   269→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7063410-9e81-4bdd-a303-eb35e073d3d0","uuid":"99057a82-0ca9-4af6-b966-89a4f3077c66","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md","content":"workflow \"finalize\" {\n  step push-for-review {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  push-for-review:success -> done\n  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n}\n```\n\nThe daemon runs `list-tasks` to discover work (output is JSONL), picks an open task,\nruns `main` with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` set, then runs `finalize` regardless of outcome.\nThe `list-tasks` script writes one JSON object per line to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`.\nThe `main` workflow receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket.\nThe `finalize` workflow decides what to do based on the outcome (available via\n`CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars).\n\n## Execution Model\n\n**Container workflows** are parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside a Docker\ncontainer. The agent walks the graph: execute current step, read its result, follow the\nwiring to the next step. This continues until a terminal (`done` or `abort`) is reached.\nAll steps run inside the same container. File state accumulates naturally across steps.\n","numLines":25,"startLine":245,"totalLines":279}}}
